## Accessing the print job indexes configuration mode
- In the **Output **settings exploration panel, select the **Files and metadata **node.

- Click the **Details **button for the configuration you wish to access.

Or:

- In the **Output **settings exploration panel, expand the **Files and metadata **node and click on the name of the required setting.

- Open the **Print job settings **tab to access the configuration of print job indexes.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

## Managing print job indexes
### Creating a print job index
- Access the print job indexes configuration mode for the required file and metadata settings.

- Click &nbsp;![](data:image/png;base64,) to create a new Index.

- Enter a code for the index in the **New index **window.

![](data:image/png;base64,)	

- Indicate whether this index must be created as a physical index or if the corresponding information must be added to the spool as TLE tags.

> Warning

This latter option is only available when the spool file is of AFPDS OR PDF type.

- Click **New **or press **Enter **to confirm the creation and close the window.

> Warning

The index creation window performs a validation on the code entered. If the code field is empty or is the same as another code already used in the Serializer, creation is not possible.

### Deleting a print job index
- Access the print job indexes configuration mode for the required file and metadata settings.

- Click the name of the index you wish to delete.

- Click &nbsp;![](data:image/png;base64,) to delete the index.

- In the confirmation prompt window, click **Delete **to confirm the operation and close the window.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

### Changing the code of a print job index
- Access the print job indexes configuration mode for the required file and metadata settings.

- Click the name of the index you wish to modify.

- Click **Change **next to the Identifier box.

- Enter a code for the index in the **Change index **window.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

- Click **Apply **to confirm the change and close the window.

> Warning

The index modification window performs a validation on the code entered. If the code field is empty or is the same as another code already used in the Serializer, the change is not possible.

### Changing the properties of a print job index
**![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)**

- Access the print job indexes configuration mode for the required file and metadata settings.

- Indicate whether this index must be created as a physical index (**Placed in a separate file**) or if the corresponding information must be added to the spool as TLE tags (**Placed inside the spool (AFPDS or PDF only**).

> Warning

The latter option is only available when the spool file is of AFPDS or PDF type.

- Click the name of the index you wish to modify.

- Enter the text of choice for the **Name**.

- Drag a String type attribute from the allowed attributes panel into the **File name **box.

- To enable the Index, select **Enable**.

- Select the desired characters encoding by selecting one of the **Encoding **values.

- Select the **Hierarchical **checkbox to allow the nesting of index records.

> Warning

The nesting structure is dictated by the hierarchy of the entities that generate the events (the print job encloses shipments, which enclose documents, etc.). The hierarchical index is only supported by PDF spools when the index is created inside the spool. It can also generate a set of PDF bookmarks that can be used to navigate the pages in a PDF reader program.

> Warning

A file name must be supplied for each index.

## The index structure
The index structure is hierarchical and consists of the items described below.

**Name**

**Icon**

**Description**

**Group of indexes**

![](data:image/png;base64,)

Groups the indexes by category. There is one group of indexes for print jobs, one for Spool Sets and one for Spool Files.

**Index**

![](data:image/png;base64,)

Represents just one index. Allows modification of properties such as the file name.

**Occurrence**

![](data:image/png;base64,)

Requires content to be emitted on the index when a specific event occurs during generation of the print spool.

**Record**

![](data:image/png;base64,)

For each occurrence one or more records can be linked to the index containing the information to be traced.

### Creating an occurrence for a print job index
- Access the print job indexes configuration mode for the required file and metadata settings.

- Click the name of the index to which you wish to add an occurrence.

- Click &nbsp;![](data:image/png;base64,) to add the occurrence.

- In the **Create **window, select the event on which you wish to set the occurrence from the Event menu.

![](data:image/png;base64,) 

- Click **Create **or press **Enter **to confirm the creation and close the window.

> Warning

No more than one occurrence can be created on each index for each event available. If you have already created one or more occurrences, their events will no longer be available when additional occurrences are created for the same inde

### Deleting an occurrence for a print job index
- Access the print job indexes configuration mode for the required file and metadata settings.

- Click the name of the occurrence you wish to delete.

- Click &nbsp;![](data:image/png;base64,) to delete the occurrence.

> Warning

No confirmation is required for the deletion of an occurrence.

### Creating a record for a print job index
- Access the print job indexes configuration mode for the required file and metadata settings.

- Click the name of the occurrence to which you wish to add a record.

- Click &nbsp;![](data:image/png;base64,) to add the record.

### Changing the properties of a print job index record
- Access the print job indexes configuration mode for the required file and metadata settings.

- Click the name of the record whose properties you wish to modify.

- Enter the text of choice for the **Name**.

- Select the record terminator from the **Terminator **menu.

- Select the concatenation mode of the operands entered in the record from the **Concatenation **menu.

- If you wish to enter a separator between the operands in the record, enter the corresponding text in the **Separator **box.

 If you wish to use constant elements in the record, click the **Constant **button to add them, then click the corresponding box to modify the text.

-  If you wish to use variable elements in the record, drag them straight from the allowed attributes panel into the position required. 

-  If you wish to delete an element from the record, click the name of the element then click **Delete**.

-  If you wish to change the order of the elements in the record, drag them into the order required.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,) 

### Deleting a record for a print job index
- Access the print job indexes configuration mode for the required file and metadata settings.

- Click the name of the record you wish to delete.

- Click &nbsp;![](data:image/png;base64,) to delete the record.

> Warning

No confirmation is required for the deletion of a record.

## Configuring datasection usage logs
For each section of *Files and Metadata, *it is possible to open the log file configuration popup by clicking on the link **Data Section usage logging**. This will automatically generate a log file indicating when the bindings of a given data section will appear in the layout of a produced document.

When enabled, during the generation of a document, the binding for the selected datasections will be traced, and their positions, relative to the page section and document, will be reported in the output XML report. The report shows, for each binding:

-  the shipment and document in which it is found 

-  the full XPath

-  the values taken from the input file for all attributes of the given XPath

-  the page at which it is found (relative to the section and to the document) 

-  the name of the page set

Users can select one or more datasections that they wish to trace throughout the generation of the document by selecting the **Record usage in print **checkbox.

> Note

For more information, see: Data Properties.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Options**

**Description**

**Enable**

Enable use of the log file.

**Name of the logging file**

Set the name of the log file.

**Break file using spoolset settings**

Define whether the log file should be split according to the spool set configurations, or not.
